...since there it&#39;s clear that we&#39;re using a string and not a string literal `&quot;name&quot;`. Indexer properties let you do that, whereas without an indexer property [you get an error][1] if you do that:

&gt;     interface NumberDictionary {
&gt;     //    [index: string]: number;       commented out indexer
&gt;         length: number;
&gt;         name: string;
&gt;     }
